===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|singen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|singan|lang=ang}} 'to sing, recite', from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*singwaną}} (compare West Frisian {{term|sjonge|lang=fy}}, Low German {{term|singen|lang=nds}}, Dutch {{term|zingen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|singen|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|synge|lang=da}}, Swedish {{term|sjunga|lang=sv}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*sengʷh-}} (compare {{etyl|wlm|-}} {{term|deongl||to explain|lang=wlm}}, {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|ὁμφή||voice, oracle|tr=omphḗ|lang=grc}}, Prakrit ''saṃghai'' 'to say, teach').

