===Verb===
{{en-verb|sings|singing|'''[[sang]]'''|'''[[sung]]''' or (archaic) '''[[sungen]]'''}}<!--Sang or sung for preterite, according to AHD.-->

# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[produce]] [[musical]] or [[harmonious]] [[sound]]s with one’s [[voice]].
#: ''"I really want to '''sing''' in the school choir." said Vera''.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[express]] [[audibly]] by means of a harmonious [[vocalization]].
#* {{quote-book|1852|Mrs M.A. Thompson|chapter=The Tutor's Daughter|Graham's American Monthly Magazine of Literature, Art, and Fashion|page=266|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=hdcRAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA266
|passage=In the lightness of my heart I '''sang''' catches of songs as my horse gayly bore me along the well-remembered road.}}
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To soothe with singing.
#: ''to '''sing''' somebody to sleep''
# {{context|intransitive|slang|lang=en}} To [[confess]] under [[interrogation]].
# To make a small, shrill sound.
#: ''The air '''sings''' in passing through a crevice.''
#* Alexander Pope
#*: O'er his head the flying spear / '''Sang''' innocent, and spent its force in air.
# To relate in verse; to celebrate in poetry.
#* Prior
#*: Bid her {{...}} '''sing''' / Of human hope by cross event destroyed.
#: {{rfquotek|Milton}}

